    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Leontodon crispatus are digestive issues, such as IBS, which studies have shown can be alleviated by its anti-inflammatory properties. This plant has also been used to treat wounds and cuts due to its antimicrobial and antifungal properties, promoting faster healing and reducing the risk of infection. Leontodon crispatus has been used to alleviate respiratory issues like bronchitis, as its expectorant properties help to loosen and clear mucus from the lungs. Additionally, it has been used to treat skin conditions like eczema, due to its anti-inflammatory and antiseptic properties. Furthermore, Leontodon crispatus has been used to alleviate fever and reduce the severity of colds due to its antipyretic properties.",
