    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Leontodon crispatus are anti-inflammatory, antioxidant and antimicrobial. Its anti-inflammatory property is primarily responsible for the reduction of inflammation and pain, which is attributed to the presence of sesquiterpene lactones and flavonoids like kaempferol and quercetin. The antioxidant property of Leontodon crispatus helps in scavenging free radicals and protecting against oxidative stress, which is due to the presence of phenolic acids and saponins. The antimicrobial property of this plant exhibits strong activity against a range of microorganisms, including bacteria and fungi, which is attributed to the presence of volatile oils and saponins. The analgesic and antipyretic properties of Leontodon crispatus also contribute to its medicinal value, particularly in the treatment of fever and pain.",
