    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Leontodon crispatus are flavonoids, phenolic acids, and sesquiterpene lactones, particularly leontodin and alantolactone, which possess anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antioxidant properties. Leontodin has been shown to exhibit analgesic and anti-inflammatory activity, while alantolactone has been reported to have antibacterial and antifungal effects. The flavonoids present in Leontodon crispatus, including quercetin and kaempferol, are known for their antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties. The phenolic acids, including caffeic acid and ferulic acid, have been found to exhibit antimicrobial and antioxidant activity. These bioactive compounds contribute to the plant's potential therapeutic effects, including wound healing, anti-inflammatory responses, and antimicrobial actions.",
