    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Leontond crispatus improperly include triggering allergic reactions due to its high content of sesquiterpene lactones, which can cause an immune response in sensitive individuals. Ingestion of the plant may also induce vomiting and cause diarrhea as a result of its emetic and purgative properties. Furthermore, Leontond crispatus can cause nausea due to its irritating effect on the gastrointestinal tract. In severe cases, improper use of the plant may lead to more severe gastrointestinal issues, including diarrhea and abdominal pain. These side effects are likely to occur due to the plant's high concentration of bioactive compounds, which can interact negatively with the body's physiological systems when ingested in large quantities.",
    "family_slug": "asteraceae",
